'''Juvenile idiopathic arthritis''' (which is also called '''juvenile rheumatoid arthritis''') is a condition which affects people ages 16 and under. The problem consists of excess swelling around joints in the [[knee]]s, [[ankle]]s, wrists, [[hand]]s and feet. Symptoms consists of lethargy, strong [[pain]] and reduced physical activity. There is also stiffness in the morning which may improve later on during the day. Juvenile arthritis is autoimmune.
